To solve this problem, we need to find the minimum possible stability factor of an array after performing at most `maxC` modifications. The stability factor is defined as the length of the longest stable subarray, where a stable subarray has a greatest common divisor (GCD) of all elements greater than or equal to 2. 

### Approach
1. **Binary Search on Answer**: The solution involves performing a binary search over possible values of the stability factor (from 0 to the length of the array). For each candidate value `x`, we check if it's possible to ensure that the longest stable subarray has a length at most `x` by performing at most `maxC` modifications.
2. **Sparse Table for GCD Queries**: To efficiently compute the GCD of any subarray, we use a sparse table. This data structure allows us to compute the GCD of any subarray in logarithmic time after an initial preprocessing step.
3. **Checking Feasibility of `x`**: For each candidate `x`, we check every possible subarray of length `x+1` (since we need to ensure no stable subarray of length greater than `x` exists). If a subarray is stable (GCD ≥ 2), we mark it for modification. We use a greedy approach to cover these subarrays with minimal modifications: whenever we encounter an uncovered stable subarray, we place a modification at its end to cover it and all overlapping subarrays.

### Solution Code
```java
public static long solve(long[] nums, long maxC) {
    int n = nums.length;
    if (n == 0) return 0;

    int[] log = new int[n + 1];
    for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
        log[i] = log[i / 2] + 1;
    }

    int k = (int) (Math.log(n) / Math.log(2)) + 1;
    long[][] st = new long[n][k + 1];

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        st[i][0] = nums[i];
    }

    for (int j = 1; j <= k; j++) {
        int step = 1 << (j - 1);
        for (int i = 0; i + (1 << j) <= n; i++) {
            st[i][j] = gcd(st[i][j - 1], st[i + step][j - 1]);
        }
    }

    long low = 0, high = n;
    long ans = n;
    while (low <= high) {
        long mid = (low + high) >>> 1;
        if (check(mid, n, maxC, st, log)) {
            ans = mid;
            high = mid - 1;
        } else {
            low = mid + 1;
        }
    }
    return ans;
}

private static boolean check(long x, int n, long maxC, long[][] st, int[] log) {
    if (x >= n) return true;
    long L = x + 1;
    if (L > n) return true;
    long last = -1;
    long countMod = 0;

    for (int i = 0; i <= n - L; i++) {
        int r = i + (int) L - 1;
        int len = r - i + 1;
        int j = log[len];
        long a = st[i][j];
        long b = st[r - (1 << j) + 1][j];
        long g = gcd(a, b);

        if (g >= 2) {
            if (i > last) {
                countMod++;
                last = r;
            }
        }
    }
    return countMod <= maxC;
}

private static long gcd(long a, long b) {
    while (b != 0) {
        long temp = b;
        b = a % b;
        a = temp;
    }
    return a;
}
```

